OL,6,F"And he cannot be certain that all
OL,7,Fcost pressures have yet been
OL,8,Fidentified."
OL,10,FMs Alexander said she is "drawing a
OL,11,Fline in the sand, calling time on
OL,12,Fyears of mismanagement, flawed
OL,13,Freporting and ineffective oversight".
OL,15,FThe Transport Secretary claimed the
OL,16,Fword "affordable" was "clearly not
OL,17,Fpart of the HS2 lexicon".
OL,19,FShe went on: "This Government will get
OL,20,Fthe job done between Birmingham and
OL,21,FLondon.
